[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman critical after 'setting herself on fire' at police station

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A woman who apparently set herself on fire at a Scottish police station is in a critical condition in hospital.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The woman suffered serious burns in the incident in the reception area of Clydebank police station, in the town's Montrose Street, at 09:55 on Wednesday.
The reception area was closed while officers carried out investigations but has since re-opened.
The injured woman was attended by paramedics before being taken to Glasgow Royal Infirmary.
